      'georgy.toast.ghOnly': 'Georgy mode — greenhouse channels only',
      'georgy.guide.title': 'Detailed guide',
      'georgy.guide.scope': '<div class="georgy-guide-note"><strong>Georgy mode only</strong> adds the simplified panel, hides extra blocks, and canopy-based density fit (≤20&nbsp;mm leaf overlap). The <strong>main calculator</strong> also changed: growth/light model, removed “2 rows in channel”, default 50% row offset, default length/channels — those apply without Georgy too.</div><h4>Who it is for</h4><p>Greenhouse, 110×55&nbsp;mm channels. Head lettuce — single cut; baby arugula & lettuce — cups and multicut. Hidden: adult arugula, basil, mizuna, kale, chard, spinach, pak choi. VF and pallets disabled.</p>',
      'georgy.guide.workflow': '<h4>Workflow (follow the steps)</h4><ol><li><strong>Pick a cultivar</strong> — drives M<sub>max</sub>, growth rate, canopy, bolting.</li><li><strong>Step 1.</strong> Set grow days in channel (14–40&nbsp;d); check mass/canopy preview.</li><li><strong>Step 2.</strong> Sanity-check mass and canopy for season and cultivar.</li><li><strong>Step 3.</strong> Click <strong>Fit to canopy (no leaf touch)</strong> — density unlocks; tweak if needed.</li><li>Set <strong>useful area</strong> (m²) in the greenhouse yield block — check nominal totals, ideal scenarios (+12.5 / +17.5&nbsp;%), and the cultivar yield table.</li><li>Review <strong>layout, metrics</strong>, and warnings.</li></ol>',
      'georgy.guide.visible': '<h4>Visible vs hidden in Georgy mode</h4><table><thead><tr><th>Still available</th><th>Hidden or fixed</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Georgy panel, cultivar, channel system, layout, metrics</td><td>Nursery (0&nbsp;d), manual mass/canopy, density until fit, multicut, A/B scenarios</td></tr><tr><td>Environment (month, temp, supplemental light)</td><td>Duplicate cycle sliders in culture panel</td></tr><tr><td>Area yield (0–20&nbsp;% margin, +12.5 / +17.5&nbsp;% scenarios), farm-wide cultivar yield table, growth chart; compare curves in Growth chart when enabled</td><td>Planting calendar, GH standards, multicut block (culture panel), A/B scenario panel</td></tr></tbody></table>',
      'georgy.guide.auto': '<h4>Auto settings on each recalc</h4><table><thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Value</th><th>Why</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Germination</td><td>3&nbsp;d</td><td>Baby cycle</td></tr><tr><td>Nursery</td><td>0&nbsp;d</td><td>Direct to channel</td></tr><tr><td>Row offset</td><td>50%</td><td>2 cup rows, stagger</td></tr><tr><td>Channels wide</td><td>10–19</td><td>≤2&nbsp;m system width</td></tr><tr><td>Lighting</td><td>User toggle (Environment)</td><td>DLI affects baby norm and head model</td></tr><tr><td>Multicut (baby)</td><td>On</td><td>Cuts until replant; area yield with replacement</td></tr><tr><td>Head lettuce</td><td>1 cut</td><td>Growth model</td></tr></tbody></table>',
      'georgy.guide.step1': '<h4>Step 1 — time from sowing</h4><p><strong>Baby:</strong> channel-days slider (germination fixed 3&nbsp;d).</p><p><strong>Head lettuce:</strong> <strong>germination</strong>, <strong>nursery</strong> (excluded from useful area), <strong>channel days</strong>. Mass/canopy use <strong>total</strong> days (e.g. 3+14+20&nbsp;= 37&nbsp;d). Useful-area turnover = <strong>channel days only</strong> (15&nbsp;d → ~2 harvests/mo).</p>',
      'georgy.guide.step2': '<h4>Step 2 — mass and canopy (model)</h4><p>From M(t) and d≈c<sub>a</sub>√M, not from scales. <strong>Also change:</strong> cultivar, <em>month</em> and <em>temperature</em> in Environment — then recheck and refit density if needed.</p>',
      'georgy.guide.step3': '<h4>Step 3 — density from canopy</h4><p>Finds <strong>maximum</strong> density (pcs/m²) with <strong>no leaf touch</strong>: <strong>romaine</strong> uses top of canopy range, other head types use mid. May add <strong>extra row spacing</strong> (extraB). Manual increase: <strong>yellow</strong> up to 20&nbsp;mm overlap, <strong>red</strong> over 20&nbsp;mm.</p>',
      'georgy.guide.env': '<h4>Light and season (Environment panel)</h4><ul><li><strong>Month</strong> — natural DLI and day length.</li><li><strong>Supplemental</strong> — daytime DLI + evening to 16&nbsp;h; extra biomass in warm months.</li><li><strong>Temperature</strong> — growth multiplier and bolting.</li></ul>',
      'georgy.guide.margin': '<h4>Uncertainty</h4><ul><li><strong>Margin slider 0–20&nbsp;%</strong> (±%) in the area-yield block and at the farm compare table — spread for real batches; without it totals are the <strong>conservative (mid) scenario</strong>.</li><li>Area from manual input or “From channel geometry”.</li><li><strong>Biological spread</strong> panel may be hidden in Georgy — exit mode for full ± ranges on metrics.</li></ul>',
      'georgy.guide.yield': '<h4>Area yield and scenarios</h4><ul><li><strong>Conservative (mid) scenario</strong> — monthly/yearly yield and kg/m²·year in metrics: model <strong>nominal</strong> (no +12.5 / +17.5&nbsp;%).</li><li>Block <strong>“If conditions are ideal (vs nominal — mid scenario)”</strong>: <strong>Basic +12.5&nbsp;%</strong> and <strong>Optimistic +17.5&nbsp;%</strong> to farm totals (kg/mo and kg/yr).</li><li><strong>“Cultivar yield comparison (full area)”</strong> — with area set: kg/m²·yr, kg/m²·mo, kg/mo and kg/yr columns; each cultivar gets its own canopy fit (no leaf touch).</li><li><strong>Baby</strong> monthly/yearly yield assumes timely replanting after each cut cycle; Georgy cut plan is per plant until replacement.</li><li>Short note above the Georgy panel repeats mid vs ideal scenarios.</li></ul>',
      'georgy.guide.read': '<h4>Reading the output</h4><ul><li><strong>Layout</strong> — pitch, rows, leaf gap, canopy overlap.</li><li><strong>Metrics</strong> — mass/plant, ρ<sub>A</sub>, system width, kg/m²·year (mid scenario).</li><li><strong>Warnings</strong> — overlap &gt;20&nbsp;mm, bolting, low DLI.</li><li><strong>Compare cultivars</strong> panel — growth curves when enabled; in Georgy use the legend under Growth chart.</li></ul>',
      'georgy.guide.sources': '<h4>Model sources</h4><p>Cornell CEA Lettuce Handbook; Both&nbsp;1997; Samuoliene; Thompson&nbsp;1998; Rijk&nbsp;Zwaan datasheets. See page footer.</p>',
